Class Navigation

    • java.lang.Thread

    public class Navigation
extends java.lang.Thread
    The main thread of the project. It controls the activation of other threads when it needs them by using the flag defined in main.Global like main.Global.usSwitch

      • travelZipLine

        public void travelZipLine(boolean zone)
                   throws java.lang.Exception
        Travels the zipline. The robot has to be at the position specified by Global.zoneZipline0 or Global.oppZipline0 before calling this method. The robot then aligns itself with the zipline and traverse it.
        Parameters:
        zone - True means we traverse the zipline from our starting zone, False means from the opponent's zone
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • travelToTransit

        public void travelToTransit(boolean zone)
        Travels to the right transit point (zipline or water) depending on which zone the robot is currently in.
        Parameters:
        zone - True means we are in our own zone, False means we are in the opponent's

      • travelWater

        public void travelWater(boolean zone)
        Traverse the shallow water.
        Parameters:
        zone - True if the robot is in it's zone, False otherwise

      • findFlag

        public void findFlag()
        Makes the robot search the opponent's zone for the flag. It uses the ultrasonic sensor and both color sensors. When it finds the flag, it beeps 3 times and the method returns.

      • travelTo

        public void travelTo(int x,
                     int y)
              throws java.lang.Exception
        Make the robot travel to a given X and Y position. It first moves along the X axis, then along the Y axis. It also performs wall correction to assure the robot is moving in a straight line. It uses the left color sensor to detect lines as it's moving.
        Parameters:
        x - The target x coordinate
        y - The target y coordinate
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • move

        public void move(double distance,
                 boolean immediatereturn)
          throws java.lang.Exception
        Make the robot travel forward at a fixed speed specified by Global.MOVING_SPEED. It will travel the distance passed in centimeter. The method can wait until the distance is traveled before returning, or it can return immediately, depending on the immediatereturn flag.
        Parameters:
        distance - the distance in cm the robot has to travel
        immediatereturn - Specify if the method should wait for the wheels to be done before returning
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • turn

        public void turn(double angle,
                 boolean immediatereturn)
          throws java.lang.Exception
        Rotate the wheels in order to turn the robot in a clockwise fashion. If the angle parameter is negative, the robot will turn counter-clockwise. This method can return before the wheels are finished rotating if the immediatereturn parameter is true. Else it will wait until the wheels are done rotating.
        Parameters:
        angle - The angle specifying how much the to turn in degrees
        immediatereturn - Specify if the method should wait for the wheels to be done before returning
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • FallingEdge

        public void FallingEdge()
                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Performs the falling edge localization routine. It turns on the appropriate UltrasonicSensor thread at the start and uses the data from the sensor to localize. It turns the sensor thread off at the end.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • lightPosition

        public void lightPosition()
                   throws java.lang.Exception
        Performs a simple light positioning routine to position the robot at the intersection of two black lines, facing in the positive X direction (angle 0). It uses the left color sensor.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
